VUstad Mazhar and Jawaad Ali of Kasur Patiala Gharana will perform at Smriti Nandan in Bangalore on May 28.The artistes are the talented grandsons of the legendary Ustad Bade Ghulam Ali Khan, the doyen of the Kasur Patiala Gharana. The combination of the talent that comes with such lineage and rigorous musical training has lead to the duo performing at various venues in India and abroad. They perform together and are well respected A grade artistes of both the All India Radio and Doordarshan.Ustad Mazhar and Ustad Jawaad spent their early years imbibing the nuances of the Kasur Patiala gharana from their grandfather Ustad Bade Ghulam Ali Khan, their grand uncle Ustad Barkat Ali Khan and their father Karamat Ali Khan. They started formal musical training under their uncle and guru, Ustad Munawar Ali Khan, second son of Ustad Bade Ghulam Ali khan. He taught them the intricate Chamukhia style that is specific to the Kasur Patiala style. Their guru's vigorous talim or training stretched for many years, and the talim was coupled with many hours of daily riyaaz or practice. This rigorous training coupled with their love for music has made them the capable torch-bearers of the Kasur Patiala gharana that they are today.Donation passes at Rs. 300 and Rs. 100 for the concert is available at the venue itself beginning 5 pm. The concert is between 7 p.m. and 9 p.m. For details, call 22258091 / 65979732
